ras and that $\\mathcal{B}$ can be endowed with a Hopf\nstructure. We recognize two already known combinatorial Hopf subalgebras of\n$\\mathcal{B}$ : $\\mathrm{WSym}$ the algebra of word symmetric functions indexed\nby set partitions and $\\mathrm{BWSym}$ the algebra of biword symmetric\nfunctions indexed by set partitions into lists.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 18 Dec 2015 13:14:55 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 5 Jan 2016 15:43:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-02-09"}
